  m_Name: Forepaw_Digit1_Phalanx_R
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::ModelPartDataSO
  id: Forepaw_Digit1_Phalanx_R
  partName: Forepaw Digit1 Phalanx Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right forepaw digit one phalanx forms part of the skeletal structure of the
    first digit within the canine forepaw. This bone supports movement and positioning
    of the digit during locomotion, balance, and weight distribution. It serves as
    an attachment point for tendons and ligaments controlling flexion and extension
    of the toe.
  - Although smaller than other weight-bearing digits, the first digit contributes
    to stability and coordination during specific movements such as turning or gripping
    uneven surfaces. Proper alignment and structural integrity are important for
    smooth paw mechanics and balanced movement.
